<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-30T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-30T15:00:00-05:00" n="5" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">641.5531/19: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador to the Belgian Government in Exile</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-30T22:00:00+02:00">April 30,
                                    1942—10 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received April 30—7:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Belgian Series No. 3. Your 2, April 28, 7 p.m. I have spoken in a
                            preliminary way to Belgian Colonial Minister de Vleeschauwer <pb facs="0012" n="6" xml:id="pg_6"/> regarding problem of Congo
                            purchases and supplies and he is postponing contemplated trip to
                            Washington.</p>
                        <closer>[<signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Biddle</hi>
                            </signed>]</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>